definitions.definition: The inside of a building , container , cavern , or other enclosed structure.
examples: The gardens are just divine, but the interior of the house are even more splendid.

definitions.definition: The inside regions of a country , distanced from the borders or coasts .
examples: Sir Richard Burton explored far into the African interior .

definitions.definition: The set of all interior points of a set .

main_definition: The inside of a building , container , cavern , or other enclosed structure.
secondary_definitions: The inside regions of a country , distanced from the borders or coasts .
( mathematics , topology ) The set of all interior points of a set .
